Hollow Square Star Pattern in Java
This Java program prints a hollow square pattern made of asterisks (*), based on the size specified by the user. 
Unlike a filled square, the center of the square is empty, with only the border lines displaying stars. 
This is a great example to understand the use of conditional logic inside nested loops.


import java.util.*;
public class Squarehallow {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		int n = sc.nextInt();
		for(int i=1;i<=n;i++) {
			for(int j=1;j<=n;j++) {
				if(i==1 || i==n || j==1 || j==n) {
					System.out.print("* ");
				}
				else {
					System.out.print("  ");
				}
			}
			System.out.println();
		}

	}

}

Sample Input/Output:
5
Output:
* * * * * 
*       * 
*       * 
*       * 
* * * * * 

Nested loops for row and column control

Conditional statements (if-else) for printing stars or spaces

User input using the Scanner class

Basic pattern design logic in console-based programs


